221
00:07:39,080 --> 00:07:39,800
Buy them.

222
00:07:39,800 --> 00:07:40,380
Come.

223
00:07:40,380 --> 00:07:40,960
Let's go.

224
00:07:42,120 --> 00:07:43,240
Isn't this...

225
00:07:43,240 --> 00:07:43,560
Ding.

226
00:07:43,560 --> 00:07:44,640
Uncle Ke

227
00:07:44,640 --> 00:07:45,200
and

228
00:07:45,200 --> 00:07:45,760
And Ning.

229
00:07:45,760 --> 00:07:46,720
Ning?

230
00:07:47,880 --> 00:07:50,000
I customized two rings for you both.

231
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:51,040
Glass rings.

232
00:07:52,240 --> 00:07:53,560
I hope you two can stay together

233
00:07:54,360 --> 00:07:54,760
happily

234
00:07:54,760 --> 00:07:55,720
forever.

235
00:07:55,720 --> 00:07:56,360
Forever.

236
00:07:56,360 --> 00:07:57,260
(Butterfly)

237
00:08:02,320 --> 00:08:03,960
An Xiaoding is impressive.

238
00:08:03,960 --> 00:08:05,600
(An Xiaoding, the youngest grandson)
He's wearing luxury from head to toe.

239
00:08:09,080 --> 00:08:09,880
Mr. Wu.

240
00:08:11,920 --> 00:08:14,160
How are you still bringing me
this kind of cheap stuff?

241
00:08:14,160 --> 00:08:15,440
I've said it many times.

242
00:08:15,440 --> 00:08:16,920
I can't wear this kind of fabric.

243
00:08:18,560 --> 00:08:20,160
I only accept two things.

244
00:08:20,640 --> 00:08:23,000
Top-grade Italian cashmere

245
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:24,440
and a spoiled life.

246
00:08:29,080 --> 00:08:30,240
He's throwing trash everywhere again.

247
00:08:31,960 --> 00:08:32,720
He's been spoiled.

248
00:08:32,720 --> 00:08:34,200
He's so spoilt.

249
00:08:34,200 --> 00:08:35,550
I've been sick of An Xiaoding too.

250
00:08:35,620 --> 00:08:36,580
(I equally dislike every guy)

251
00:08:39,790 --> 00:08:41,280
Ding,

252
00:08:41,550 --> 00:08:43,550
