2256
01:10:21,000 --> 01:10:22,600
The perfume you use,

2257
01:10:22,600 --> 01:10:24,440
is it cedarwood

2258
01:10:24,440 --> 01:10:26,040
and moss?

2259
01:10:30,560 --> 01:10:31,360
Such detail.

2260
01:10:32,240 --> 01:10:33,240
He changes fragrances every day.

2261
01:10:36,320 --> 01:10:37,360
I'm the one using it.

2262
01:10:38,360 --> 01:10:39,680
It's you?

2263
01:10:39,680 --> 01:10:40,040
Then,

2264
01:10:40,680 --> 01:10:42,640
what kind of father are you to me now?

2265
01:10:44,280 --> 01:10:44,640
No, no.

2266
01:10:44,640 --> 01:10:45,820
(Add more dramatic effect)

2267
01:10:48,280 --> 01:10:49,000
"A Group-Buy Dad."

2268
01:10:49,100 --> 01:10:51,300
(His first dad and second dad
are both his dads)

2269
01:10:51,560 --> 01:10:52,600
But actually,

2270
01:10:52,600 --> 01:10:53,800
I already had my own family.

2271
01:10:53,800 --> 01:10:55,720
I got married in 2015,

2272
01:10:55,720 --> 01:10:56,800
and in 2016,

2273
01:10:56,800 --> 01:10:58,840
I already had a child.

2274
01:10:58,840 --> 01:11:00,160
So you can't admit it.

2275
01:11:00,160 --> 01:11:00,960
I understand.

2276
01:11:00,960 --> 01:11:02,680
Am I really that shameful?

2277
01:11:03,320 --> 01:11:03,840
No.

2278
01:11:03,840 --> 01:11:04,080
Wait.

2279
01:11:04,080 --> 01:11:05,960
It's not like you're that desperate
to become someone's son either, right?

2280
01:11:06,280 --> 01:11:06,800
No.

2281
01:11:06,800 --> 01:11:07,960
Do you really have to claim a dad?

2282
01:11:07,960 --> 01:11:09,320
You can just not acknowledge him.

2283
01:11:09,320 --> 01:11:10,320
You're the most tragic one here today.

2284
01:11:10,320 --> 01:11:11,680
Passed from one dad to another,

2285
01:11:11,680 --> 01:11:12,840
and the new dad doesn't even want you.

2286
01:11:15,500 --> 01:11:16,140
(Clues from Jin An's Room)

2287
01:11:16,140 --> 01:11:16,730
(Jin Xiangyu's motive for murder)

2288
01:11:16,730 --> 01:11:17,800
(To stop An Er from exposing her scandal
and affecting her inheritance rights)

2289
01:11:17,800 --> 01:11:18,620
(An Ke suspected
to be An Xiaoding's biological father)

2290
01:11:18,640 --> 01:11:19,600
Let's go to An Er's room.

2291
01:11:19,600 --> 01:11:20,720
The victim's room.

2292
01:11:20,730 --> 01:11:21,190
=Crime Scene Investigation Begins=

2293
01:11:21,200 --> 01:11:21,840
Murderer, get away.

2294
01:11:22,840 --> 01:11:23,840
Get away, murderer.

2295
01:11:23,840 --> 01:11:25,800
Wait, I want to walk
with my ex-boyfriend first.

2296
01:11:27,820 --> 01:11:29,380
(He doesn't acknowledge you.)

2297
01:11:29,840 --> 01:11:30,840
(He doesn't acknowledge you.)
You forgot everything?

2298
01:11:30,840 --> 01:11:31,680
No.

2299
01:11:31,680 --> 01:11:32,320
I...

2300
01:11:32,320 --> 01:11:32,920
I understand.

2301
01:11:32,920 --> 01:11:33,720
Let's go.

2302
01:11:33,720 --> 01:11:35,900
(He doesn't acknowledge you.)

2303
01:11:36,320 --> 01:11:38,440
At least we have Autumn in My Heart.

2304
01:11:38,440 --> 01:11:39,560
And what are you supposed to be?

2305
01:11:39,560 --> 01:11:41,400
Autumn in My Heart.

2306
01:11:48,160 --> 01:11:49,320
An Er's room.

2307
01:11:49,540 --> 01:11:52,260
(New Area Unlocked: An Er's Room)

2308
01:11:56,840 --> 01:11:58,040
Whose phone is this?

2309
01:11:59,940 --> 01:12:00,780
(An Er's Phone)

2310
01:12:00,800 --> 01:12:02,720
This is An Er's phone.

2311
01:12:02,720 --> 01:12:03,560
Let's take a look.

2312
01:12:05,480 --> 01:12:09,080
March 16th, 2016, 10 PM.

2313
01:12:09,080 --> 01:12:10,440
On the 24th,

2314
01:12:10,440 --> 01:12:11,320
the next chairman will be announced.

2315
01:12:11,320 --> 01:12:13,000
He Jiahuan, An Xiaowen,
Jin Xiangyu, An Xiaoding,

2316
01:12:13,000 --> 01:12:13,960
these people could become obstacles.

2317
01:12:13,960 --> 01:12:15,200
I need dirt on all of them.

2318
01:12:15,200 --> 01:12:15,960
The more explosive, the better.

2319
01:12:16,200 --> 01:12:18,080
March 17th, 2016,

2320
01:12:18,080 --> 01:12:18,960
8 p.m.

2321
01:12:18,960 --> 01:12:20,800
I hacked
into your home surveillance system.

2322
01:12:20,800 --> 01:12:22,240
Honestly, the footage is wild.

2323
01:12:22,240 --> 01:12:23,600
See for yourself.

2324
01:12:24,280 --> 01:12:24,880
Come.

2325
01:12:26,120 --> 01:12:26,800
Listen to me.

2326
01:12:27,920 --> 01:12:29,000
As for the heir issue,

2327
01:12:29,000 --> 01:12:30,480
don't even consider Jin Xiangyu anymore.

2328
01:12:32,000 --> 01:12:33,400
The moment I saw her taste in men,

2329
01:12:33,960 --> 01:12:35,000
I knew she was no good.

2330
01:12:36,720 --> 01:12:38,960
Her ex-boyfriend is An Er's subordinate.

2331
01:12:38,960 --> 01:12:40,400
An Er's subordinate?

2332
01:12:40,400 --> 01:12:42,400
Yeah, my ex-boyfriend worked under An Er.

2333
01:12:42,400 --> 01:12:43,320
Shi Wu'ai.

2334
01:12:43,660 --> 01:12:45,120
(Jin Xiangyu's ex-boyfriend: Shi Wu'ai)
According to An Er,

2335
01:12:45,120 --> 01:12:46,200
(An Er's subordinate)
that man was also involved

2336
01:12:46,200 --> 01:12:47,400
in the poisoned-glass incident
back in '92.

2337
01:12:48,020 --> 01:12:49,820
(Poisoned glass?)

2338
01:12:49,840 --> 01:12:50,680
Then he got involved with Wu,

2339
01:12:51,080 --> 01:12:52,120
did all sorts of disgraceful things,

2340
01:12:52,120 --> 01:12:53,280
and even had a child together.

2341
01:12:53,280 --> 01:12:53,920
Me?

2342
01:12:53,920 --> 01:12:54,880
Yeah, him.

2343
01:12:55,440 --> 01:12:57,520
I already showed mercy

2344
01:12:57,520 --> 01:12:58,960
by merely kicking that child
out of the An family.

2345
01:12:59,640 --> 01:13:00,960
Kicked out of the An family?

2346
01:13:01,440 --> 01:13:02,480
Then why am I still in the An family?

2347
01:13:02,480 --> 01:13:03,960
He didn't kick you out.

2348
01:13:04,400 --> 01:13:06,240
(Something's off!)
"I already showed mercy..."

2349
01:13:09,240 --> 01:13:10,200
As for Jin Xiangyu,

2350
01:13:11,560 --> 01:13:13,040
she's nothing more
than a money-making tool to me.

2351
01:13:13,560 --> 01:13:15,360
What I want is her brain
and her ability.

2352
01:13:15,420 --> 01:13:16,300
(Sympathy)

2353
01:13:16,300 --> 01:13:17,660
(Concern, Pity)

2354
01:13:17,780 --> 01:13:18,640
(Not a shred of love?)

2355
01:13:18,640 --> 01:13:20,400
If she knew what was good for her,

2356
01:13:20,400 --> 01:13:21,600
she'd understand

2357
01:13:22,520 --> 01:13:24,120
that being allowed to stay
in the An family until now

2358
01:13:24,120 --> 01:13:25,440
is already the last bit
of dignity I'm giving her.

2359
01:13:27,600 --> 01:13:28,400
Alright, that's it for now.

2360
01:13:29,240 --> 01:13:30,840
I'll send the rest to your email later.

2361
01:13:31,520 --> 01:13:32,840
He kicked out the child

2362
01:13:32,840 --> 01:13:33,560
you and Wu,

2363
01:13:33,560 --> 01:13:35,440
which is me, had together.

2364
01:13:35,460 --> 01:13:37,500
(But I'm still here.)

2365
01:13:37,840 --> 01:13:38,920
So is it possible

2366
01:13:38,920 --> 01:13:40,960
that he's not actually the child
of the two of us?

2367
01:13:45,480 --> 01:13:46,440
Then whose child am I?

2368
01:13:46,440 --> 01:13:47,360
Where is my real father?

2369
01:13:47,940 --> 01:13:49,100
(Whose child am I, really?)

2370
01:13:49,140 --> 01:13:50,700
(This completely broke Mom's brain.)

2371
01:13:50,720 --> 01:13:51,560
Were you ever kicked out?

2372
01:13:51,560 --> 01:13:52,480
No.

2373
01:13:52,480 --> 01:13:53,040
I've always been here.

2374
01:13:53,040 --> 01:13:54,240
You grew up here, right?

2375
01:13:54,240 --> 01:13:55,240
Since childhood.

2376
01:13:55,240 --> 01:13:56,960
Then there's one possibility.

2377
01:13:56,960 --> 01:13:58,240
Your biological son

2378
01:13:58,240 --> 01:13:59,640
may have actually been sent away.

2379
01:13:59,640 --> 01:14:00,520
And another child was swapped in.

2380
01:14:00,520 --> 01:14:00,920
Exactly.

2381
01:14:01,320 --> 01:14:02,640
Okay, this is getting complicated.

2382
01:14:03,080 --> 01:14:04,120
How did this suddenly happen?

2383
01:14:04,120 --> 01:14:05,600
Can I ask
who your ex-boyfriend is again?

2384
01:14:05,600 --> 01:14:06,080
What's his name?

2385
01:14:06,080 --> 01:14:07,320
Shi Wu'ai.

2386
01:14:07,320 --> 01:14:08,960
My relationship with that ex
was really strange.

2387
01:14:08,960 --> 01:14:10,280
We dated for a long time,

2388
01:14:10,280 --> 01:14:12,000
then one day he suddenly disappeared.

2389
01:14:12,000 --> 01:14:13,360
That's why I went drinking.

2390
01:14:13,360 --> 01:14:14,840
And then you ended up...

2391
01:14:15,300 --> 01:14:16,860
(That's right, it's just that magical.)

2392
01:14:16,940 --> 01:14:18,140
(Absolutely explosive.)

2393
01:14:19,940 --> 01:14:21,100
(But Uncle Er's bed finally gave out.)

2394
01:14:21,120 --> 01:14:21,440
Wait.

2395
01:14:22,120 --> 01:14:22,520
You okay?

2396
01:14:22,520 --> 01:14:23,240
I'm fine.

2397
01:14:23,240 --> 01:14:23,720
Careful!

2398
01:14:23,720 --> 01:14:23,960
I'm fine.

2399
01:14:23,960 --> 01:14:24,680
Are you alright?

2400
01:14:24,680 --> 01:14:25,560
I'm okay.

2401
01:14:25,560 --> 01:14:27,000
How did the bed collapse?

2402
01:14:27,000 --> 01:14:27,840
We sat it to death.

2403
01:14:28,280 --> 01:14:29,520
Is there some kind
of mechanism underneath?

2404
01:14:30,200 --> 01:14:31,200
No.

2405
01:14:31,200 --> 01:14:31,880
It literally just...

2406
01:14:31,880 --> 01:14:32,600
Collapsed from sitting on it.

2407
01:14:32,600 --> 01:14:33,840
It simply couldn't handle

2408
01:14:33,840 --> 01:14:34,800
the weight of three grown men.

2409
01:14:34,800 --> 01:14:36,240
Just straight-up collapsed.

2410
01:14:36,240 --> 01:14:36,560
Right.

2411
01:14:37,520 --> 01:14:38,840
"I'll send the rest
to your email later."

2412
01:14:39,920 --> 01:14:40,520
Email?

2413
01:14:40,520 --> 01:14:41,560
Go check if there's email access.

2414
01:14:41,560 --> 01:14:42,400
See if there's email.

2415
01:14:43,120 --> 01:14:43,960
Then there should be a computer.

2416
01:14:44,680 --> 01:14:45,920
Probably something computer-related.

2417
01:14:45,920 --> 01:14:46,400
Nothing here.

2418
01:14:47,200 --> 01:14:47,520
Drawers.

2419
01:14:47,520 --> 01:14:48,000
Check the drawers.

2420
01:14:50,000 --> 01:14:51,320
Drawer.

2421
01:14:52,920 --> 01:14:53,800
There's a laptop here.

2422
01:14:56,760 --> 01:14:58,240
Back then, that woman Ning got pregnant.

2423
01:14:59,480 --> 01:15:00,960
That woman Ning?

2424
01:15:01,540 --> 01:15:02,400
(My woman?)

2425
01:15:02,400 --> 01:15:03,960
You had a woman back then?

2426
01:15:03,960 --> 01:15:05,040
Keep reading.

2427
01:15:05,040 --> 01:15:06,520
That woman Ning got pregnant.

2428
01:15:06,520 --> 01:15:08,200
She was only one
of Er's subordinates.

2429
01:15:08,200 --> 01:15:09,280
But Er said

2430
01:15:09,280 --> 01:15:10,720
she was also involved

2431
01:15:10,720 --> 01:15:12,360
in the 1992 poisoned-glass incident.

2432
01:15:12,500 --> 01:15:13,920
(Ning's woman was involved
in the poisoned-glass case?)

2433
01:15:13,920 --> 01:15:16,160
I never expected she secretly
got pregnant with Ning's child.

2434
01:15:17,040 --> 01:15:19,080
(I had a child too?!)
Ning never knew about it.

2435
01:15:19,080 --> 01:15:21,600
I paid someone to silence her

2436
01:15:21,600 --> 01:15:23,160
and had the child brought to me.

2437
01:15:23,160 --> 01:15:25,840
Coincidentally, Jin Xiangyu
also gave birth to that scoundrel.

2438
01:15:25,940 --> 01:15:27,620
(He called me a scoundrel!)

2439
01:15:27,640 --> 01:15:29,840
Didn't she cuckold me?

2440
01:15:29,840 --> 01:15:31,840
Then I'll make her raise my grandson.

2441
01:15:32,520 --> 01:15:34,920
You're his grandson.

2442
01:15:35,500 --> 01:15:37,740
(An Xiaoning and An Xiaoding
are father and son?)

2443
01:15:40,840 --> 01:15:42,160
(The spoiled younger brother)
A shattered butterfly.

2444
01:15:42,160 --> 01:15:44,200
(Turns out they're biologically related)
Who are you calling Dad?!

2445
01:15:44,200 --> 01:15:45,360
Exactly.

2446
01:15:45,360 --> 01:15:46,800
Who's your dad then?

2447
01:15:47,300 --> 01:15:48,400
(It started as a joke)

2448
01:15:48,400 --> 01:15:49,640
Wait, it actually means that?

2449
01:15:49,640 --> 01:15:51,080
No, that's not what I meant.

2450
01:15:51,080 --> 01:15:52,600
(A joke becomes reality)
How did this turn into a family drama?

2451
01:15:53,060 --> 01:15:54,680
(Absolutely insane.)
But haven't I been calling you brother?

2452
01:15:54,680 --> 01:15:56,640
Now call him "Brother-Dad."

2453
01:15:58,040 --> 01:15:59,680
He calls you little brother,
and you call him Dad.

2454
01:15:59,680 --> 01:16:00,640
(Everyone uses their own title.)

2455
01:16:00,640 --> 01:16:01,960
Time to recognize a new father.

2456
01:16:02,300 --> 01:16:03,480
(Brief father-son bond: ended.)

2457
01:16:03,480 --> 01:16:04,320
Whose dad is whose dad anymore?

2458
01:16:05,840 --> 01:16:07,160
Back in 1992,

2459
01:16:07,160 --> 01:16:08,560
I met a woman

2460
01:16:08,560 --> 01:16:10,400
named Qian Nvyou.

2461
01:16:11,560 --> 01:16:13,840
Then I really fell for her.

2462
01:16:13,840 --> 01:16:14,600
We got together,

2463
01:16:14,600 --> 01:16:15,800
even preparing to get married.

2464
01:16:15,800 --> 01:16:17,400
Then one day she told me,

2465
01:16:18,120 --> 01:16:18,720
"I'm going

2466
01:16:18,720 --> 01:16:19,920
to give you a surprise."

2467
01:16:20,840 --> 01:16:22,200
And her surprise was disappearing.

2468
01:16:22,200 --> 01:16:23,840
(An Xiaoning's ex-girlfriend
suddenly vanished.)

2469
01:16:23,840 --> 01:16:24,800
She ran away.

2470
01:16:24,800 --> 01:16:26,920
From then on,
I shut myself off emotionally.

2471
01:16:26,920 --> 01:16:28,280
I didn't date for over ten years.

2472
01:16:28,280 --> 01:16:29,720
Actually, decades.

2473
01:16:29,720 --> 01:16:31,280
That "surprise" was me.

2474
01:16:31,280 --> 01:16:32,200
(The surprise itself.)

2475
01:16:32,200 --> 01:16:34,040
She was actually planning
to surprise him with the child,

2476
01:16:34,040 --> 01:16:35,600
but never expected the child
to get taken away.

2477
01:16:35,600 --> 01:16:36,240
Right.

2478
01:16:36,240 --> 01:16:38,920
Then last year I met another girl

2479
01:16:38,920 --> 01:16:40,720
named Xi Hu.

2480
01:16:40,720 --> 01:16:42,040
Xi Hu?

2481
01:16:42,040 --> 01:16:42,800
Laundry detergent?

2482
01:16:42,800 --> 01:16:44,920
And after dating her for a year,

2483
01:16:44,920 --> 01:16:46,520
we had a child too.

2484
01:16:46,760 --> 01:16:47,800
Young Master,

2485
01:16:47,800 --> 01:16:51,200
your wife has returned
to the country with your child.

2486
01:16:51,200 --> 01:16:51,840
She came back?

2487
01:16:52,480 --> 01:16:53,840
Now this proves one thing.

2488
01:16:54,840 --> 01:16:55,200
You...

2489
01:16:56,400 --> 01:16:57,520
I am your son.

2490
01:16:57,520 --> 01:16:58,120
(Completely accepting his identity.)

2491
01:16:58,120 --> 01:16:58,480
Exactly.

2492
01:16:59,740 --> 01:17:00,460
(Hug)

2493
01:17:00,480 --> 01:17:01,600
Come here, son.

2494
01:17:03,320 --> 01:17:04,520
Call him Dad already.

2495
01:17:04,540 --> 01:17:05,420
(Struggling little feet)

2496
01:17:05,420 --> 01:17:06,860
(Accepting fate)

2497
01:17:09,480 --> 01:17:10,400
Fa...

2498
01:17:11,960 --> 01:17:12,360
Son.

2499
01:17:12,360 --> 01:17:14,000
I never thought after all these years,

2500
01:17:14,000 --> 01:17:15,280
I'd finally find you.

2501
01:17:15,280 --> 01:17:17,080
(A father pouring out his heart)
I never knew I had a son either.

2502
01:17:17,080 --> 01:17:18,880
I feel so happy right now.

2503
01:17:18,880 --> 01:17:20,080
Where's my mom?

2504
01:17:21,400 --> 01:17:23,040
From now on, I'm your grandma.

2505
01:17:25,160 --> 01:17:25,600
It's okay.

2506
01:17:25,600 --> 01:17:27,040
I know this may be hard to accept.

2507
01:17:27,040 --> 01:17:27,920
Sit down first.

2508
01:17:31,280 --> 01:17:32,200
If you can't adjust yet,

2509
01:17:32,200 --> 01:17:33,480
(still escalating the madness)
you can also call me "mommy."

2510
01:17:33,480 --> 01:17:34,920
Call her "Mom" in the morning,
and at night, call her...

2511
01:17:34,920 --> 01:17:35,940
(Sounded like sleep-talking)

2512
01:17:37,640 --> 01:17:38,560
I received a text.

2513
01:17:39,600 --> 01:17:40,520
I found it.

2514
01:17:40,520 --> 01:17:41,520
It's insanely explosive.

2515
01:17:41,520 --> 01:17:42,560
About He,

2516
01:17:45,360 --> 01:17:47,560
the biological child
of "Old Wang Next Door".

2517
01:17:47,560 --> 01:17:48,720
He Jiahuan

2518
01:17:48,720 --> 01:17:50,920
(Detective Agency Investigation)
actually died at the age of one.

2519
01:17:57,080 --> 01:17:58,760
Died at one year old?

2520
01:17:59,400 --> 01:18:00,420
(Then who am I?)
You're not him either.

2521
01:18:01,040 --> 01:18:02,680
You're the child who was abandoned.

2522
01:18:02,740 --> 01:18:04,660
(Child)

2523
01:18:04,820 --> 01:18:06,780
(Terrified child)

2524
01:18:06,840 --> 01:18:09,160
Later, they found an abandoned baby.

2525
01:18:15,080 --> 01:18:16,320
After investigation,
that child turned out to be

2526
01:18:16,320 --> 01:18:18,440
the son of Jin Xiangyu and An Ke.

2527
01:18:18,440 --> 01:18:20,920
I won't say anymore.

2528
01:18:20,920 --> 01:18:23,160
My son…

2529
01:18:23,160 --> 01:18:24,440
(Uncle's getting emotional)

2530
01:18:24,440 --> 01:18:25,680
I won't say anymore.

2531
01:18:25,680 --> 01:18:27,460
My son.

2532
01:18:30,240 --> 01:18:31,120
Uncle An Ke.

2533
01:18:31,120 --> 01:18:32,600
(A momentary title confusion.)

2534
01:18:32,600 --> 01:18:33,480
(Blood ties can't stay hidden forever)
Uncle An Ke.

2535
01:18:34,160 --> 01:18:35,800
I seriously won't say anymore.

2536
01:18:37,200 --> 01:18:38,800
My son.

2537
01:18:38,800 --> 01:18:39,440
Dad! Mom!

2538
01:18:39,440 --> 01:18:41,600
My son.

2539
01:18:41,600 --> 01:18:42,760
(Eyes opened wide today, huh?)

2540
01:18:42,760 --> 01:18:45,480
I finally found you.

2541
01:18:45,780 --> 01:18:48,220
(What other insanity is left?)

2542
01:18:48,240 --> 01:18:50,320
Wait, if I'm not biologically related...

2543
01:18:50,320 --> 01:18:52,400
Then the two of us
can be together again.

2544
01:18:52,400 --> 01:18:54,440
Daughter-in-law.

2545
01:18:54,440 --> 01:18:56,000
(We're not divorcing anymore!)
Daughter-in-law.

2546
01:18:56,000 --> 01:18:57,480
You two are siblings.

2547
01:18:57,480 --> 01:18:59,280
(Forbidden love can be exciting)
And you still fell for him?

2548
01:18:59,280 --> 01:19:01,120
(But healthy relationships matter too)

2549
01:19:01,120 --> 01:19:01,720
Dad.

2550
01:19:01,720 --> 01:19:03,840
Come, let's sit here
and watch their drama unfold.

2551
01:19:03,840 --> 01:19:06,080
(Front-row rock concert seats)
This is great! My grandson

2552
01:19:06,080 --> 01:19:08,320
wasn't born from inbreeding.

2553
01:19:08,320 --> 01:19:10,680
And you found your own son too.

2554
01:19:11,280 --> 01:19:12,800
These people are outsiders.

2555
01:19:12,800 --> 01:19:13,360
All outsiders.

2556
01:19:13,420 --> 01:19:14,560
(What does that even mean?)

2557
01:19:14,560 --> 01:19:17,080
None of you qualify for the inheritance.

2558
01:19:17,080 --> 01:19:17,760
Right.

2559
01:19:17,760 --> 01:19:19,240
You don't qualify either.

2560
01:19:19,240 --> 01:19:20,120
I'm fine just enjoying life.

2561
01:19:20,120 --> 01:19:20,640
Exactly.

2562
01:19:20,640 --> 01:19:21,120
(So enlightened.)
I mainly care because

2563
01:19:21,120 --> 01:19:23,280
I'm a legitimate member
of the An family now.

2564
01:19:23,280 --> 01:19:23,880
Exactly.

2565
01:19:24,460 --> 01:19:25,160
(Pureblood An family member.)

2566
01:19:25,160 --> 01:19:26,360
Who even are you people?

2567
01:19:27,600 --> 01:19:29,240
No, I'm an An family member too.

2568
01:19:29,240 --> 01:19:30,600
Right, Uncle Er is dead now,

2569
01:19:30,600 --> 01:19:32,600
so the inheritance falls to me, right?

2570
01:19:32,600 --> 01:19:33,700
(Hands on hips.)
Our An family fortune

2571
01:19:33,700 --> 01:19:34,430
is going to my little sister.

2572
01:19:34,780 --> 01:19:36,320
(Hands on hips.)
You're a generation younger than me.

2573
01:19:36,320 --> 01:19:37,880
I'm not obsessed with money.

2574
01:19:38,800 --> 01:19:39,520
You're my brother.

2575
01:19:39,520 --> 01:19:40,680
Wait, you're also my uncle, right?

2576
01:19:40,680 --> 01:19:41,200
Exactly.

2577
01:19:41,200 --> 01:19:43,040
We're uncle and nephew now.

2578
01:19:43,180 --> 01:19:43,920
(Awkward smile)

2579
01:19:43,920 --> 01:19:44,680
Okay.

2580
01:19:44,680 --> 01:19:46,520
No, hold on.

2581
01:19:46,520 --> 01:19:48,040
(Will someone control these detectives?)
You two detectives

2582
01:19:48,040 --> 01:19:49,080
don't even have inheritance rights.

2583
01:19:50,720 --> 01:19:52,440
(Breaking composure)
Exactly.

2584
01:19:53,680 --> 01:19:55,120
(Let's sort this out first)
They are direct descendants.

2585
01:19:55,120 --> 01:19:56,800
They're the next generation down.

2586
01:19:56,800 --> 01:19:58,960
We're the grandchildren.

2587
01:19:59,400 --> 01:20:00,200
The grandchildren generation.

2588
01:20:01,560 --> 01:20:02,960
Your generation rank is the lowest.

2589
01:20:02,960 --> 01:20:04,000
I'm the same generation as you.

2590
01:20:04,000 --> 01:20:05,280
My rank is the lowest?

2591
01:20:05,280 --> 01:20:05,960
Yep, the lowest.

2592
01:20:05,960 --> 01:20:07,720
I'm her son.

2593
01:20:09,960 --> 01:20:11,160
She's your grandmother.

2594
01:20:12,280 --> 01:20:13,840
(You during Lunar New Year visits:)
So do I call him Uncle?

2595
01:20:14,240 --> 01:20:15,600
Yeah, that's right.

2596
01:20:16,000 --> 01:20:17,040
I have to call you Uncle.

2597
01:20:18,440 --> 01:20:19,680
Why's your seniority so low?

2598
01:20:19,680 --> 01:20:21,400
Even if my rank is low,
I'm still your dad.

2599
01:20:21,400 --> 01:20:22,280
(How dare you!)
Show some respect.

2600
01:20:22,280 --> 01:20:24,440
It's okay. In the end,
everything's still mine anyway.

2601
01:20:24,440 --> 01:20:25,320
(I'll outlive all of you.)

2602
01:20:25,320 --> 01:20:26,080
(How filial)
Alright.

2603
01:20:26,400 --> 01:20:27,520
(Ke's son, Ning's younger brother)
Then I have inheritance rights too.

2604
01:20:27,520 --> 01:20:28,520
You do!

2605
01:20:28,520 --> 01:20:29,160
Then how about this?

2606
01:20:29,160 --> 01:20:31,160
The four of us team up
and secure the inheritance together.

2607
01:20:31,160 --> 01:20:31,520
Exactly.

2608
01:20:31,520 --> 01:20:32,360
We'll live a good life together.

2609
01:20:33,320 --> 01:20:33,800
Wait a second.

2610
01:20:33,800 --> 01:20:35,360
The four of us are on the same side.

2611
01:20:35,360 --> 01:20:35,960
So...

2612
01:20:35,960 --> 01:20:36,720
No, listen.

2613
01:20:37,720 --> 01:20:38,800
The four of us are together.

2614
01:20:38,800 --> 01:20:39,920
Only those two are outsiders.

2615
01:20:39,920 --> 01:20:40,880
You two are the outsiders now.

2616
01:20:40,880 --> 01:20:41,940
(Father-son. Uncle-nephew. Father-son)

2617
01:20:42,880 --> 01:20:44,520
Honey, c'mon.

2618
01:20:44,520 --> 01:20:44,760
We are...

2619
01:20:44,760 --> 01:20:45,240
(Married couple)

2620
01:20:45,240 --> 01:20:45,920
Oh, stop it.

2621
01:20:45,920 --> 01:20:46,880
Honey.

2622
01:20:47,360 --> 01:20:49,080
We still have little Anwen too.

2623
01:20:50,240 --> 01:20:51,160
That's true.

2624
01:20:51,160 --> 01:20:51,840
That's really true.

2625
01:20:51,840 --> 01:20:52,820
(Father-son. Uncle-nephew)
How did this somehow turn

2626
01:20:52,820 --> 01:20:53,760
(Father-son. Couple. Mother-son)
into one giant family?

2627
01:20:53,760 --> 01:20:54,440
Exactly.

2628
01:20:54,440 --> 01:20:55,480
We were family all along.

2629
01:20:55,480 --> 01:20:56,280
We really were one big family.

2630
01:20:56,640 --> 01:20:58,720
No wonder I liked this kid so much.

2631
01:20:59,760 --> 01:21:01,040
The more I look at him,
the more affectionate I feel.

2632
01:21:03,560 --> 01:21:04,480
How did you

2633
01:21:04,480 --> 01:21:05,000
(Feeling sorry for my son)
change sides that fast?

2634
01:21:05,000 --> 01:21:06,720
You two lived together
for twenty-three years.

2635
01:21:06,720 --> 01:21:07,240
How could you...

2636
01:21:07,240 --> 01:21:09,360
Honestly, there was always a bit
of emotional distance between us.

2637
01:21:09,360 --> 01:21:10,640
(Are you even human?)
We were actually far apart.

2638
01:21:11,160 --> 01:21:12,360
(Shattered)
Okay, and now suddenly...

2639
01:21:12,360 --> 01:21:13,760
Your son
buys you designer fashion every day.

2640
01:21:13,760 --> 01:21:15,120
(BarBer)
Everything you're wearing,

2641
01:21:15,120 --> 01:21:15,800
who bought it for you?

2642
01:21:15,800 --> 01:21:16,800
I bought it all myself.

2643
01:21:18,560 --> 01:21:20,560
It's okay. Your new son
can buy things for you now too.

2644
01:21:20,960 --> 01:21:21,600
My son.

2645
01:21:26,120 --> 01:21:28,320
This eldest son really is lovable.

2646
01:21:28,320 --> 01:21:30,740
(Look at that expression.)
No wonder he's so tall.

2647
01:21:30,740 --> 01:21:32,440
No wonder he's so tall.

2648
01:21:32,440 --> 01:21:34,080
Who did you inherit

2649
01:21:34,080 --> 01:21:35,320
that giant height from?

2650
01:21:39,540 --> 01:21:40,470
(Yi & Jin: married (second wife);
Yi & Er: brothers)

2651
01:21:40,470 --> 01:21:41,000
(Er & Ke: brothers;
Jin & Ding: mother-son)

2652
01:21:41,000 --> 01:21:41,620
(Yi & Ning/Wen:
father-son/daughter (first wife))

2653
01:21:41,620 --> 01:21:42,330
(Ning & Wen: siblings;
Wen & He: married)

2654
01:21:42,330 --> 01:21:42,900
(Yi & Er & Ke: brothers;
Ke & Jin: past affair)

2655
01:21:42,900 --> 01:21:43,740
(Ning & Ding: father-son;
Yi & Ning: father-son (first wife))

2656
01:21:43,740 --> 01:21:44,930
(Ning & He: cousins;
He: son of Ke & Jin)

2657
01:21:44,950 --> 01:21:45,740
(Wen & He: married)

2658
01:21:46,600 --> 01:21:47,480
New messages are coming in.

2659
01:21:48,200 --> 01:21:48,960
Here.

2660
01:21:48,960 --> 01:21:49,560
Mr. An,

2661
01:21:50,200 --> 01:21:51,560
(Truth Detective Agency)
just like you predicted,

2662
01:21:51,560 --> 01:21:53,440
someone's looking

2663
01:21:53,440 --> 01:21:55,280
into the 1992 An Glass Factory

2664
01:21:55,280 --> 01:21:56,440
toxic glass incident.

2665
01:21:56,440 --> 01:21:58,520
That person has already entered
the An family.

2666
01:21:58,620 --> 01:22:00,900
(Someone's digging
into that toxic glass case?)

2667
01:22:03,320 --> 01:22:05,360
So that means...

2668
01:22:05,360 --> 01:22:06,520
Someone's watching us right now.

2669
01:22:09,600 --> 01:22:10,760
There's something up there.

2670
01:22:19,080 --> 01:22:19,800
It's an iPad.

2671
01:22:19,800 --> 01:22:20,120
Unlock it.

2672
01:22:20,120 --> 01:22:20,840
iPad.

2673
01:22:22,840 --> 01:22:24,520
Magazine shoot group chat.

2674
01:22:24,520 --> 01:22:25,040
For coordination.

2675
01:22:25,040 --> 01:22:26,160
We're in the chat.

2676
01:22:26,160 --> 01:22:26,520
Go on.

2677
01:22:27,280 --> 01:22:29,440
On March 21,
An Er started the group chat.

2678
01:22:29,440 --> 01:22:31,400
The set design for the shoot

2679
01:22:31,400 --> 01:22:32,320
is finalized.

2680
01:22:32,320 --> 01:22:34,680
He Jiahuan and Jin Xiangyu,

2681
01:22:34,680 --> 01:22:36,120
handle the stage setup.

2682
01:22:36,560 --> 01:22:37,680
Follow my design.

2683
01:22:37,680 --> 01:22:38,480
(Responsible for stage setup.)

2684
01:22:38,480 --> 01:22:39,640
Got it.

2685
01:22:39,640 --> 01:22:41,200
March 24, 9:30 a.m.

2686
01:22:41,200 --> 01:22:42,920
Today, right?

2687
01:22:42,920 --> 01:22:44,440
Half an hour earlier.

2688
01:22:44,960 --> 01:22:46,040
Hello, Mr. An.

2689
01:22:46,040 --> 01:22:47,280
The stage setup is complete.

2690
01:22:47,280 --> 01:22:48,520
Mr. He and Ms. Jin

2691
01:22:48,520 --> 01:22:49,320
have checked everything.

2692
01:22:49,320 --> 01:22:51,040
No one has been here since.

2693
01:22:51,040 --> 01:22:52,640
You can come to the set now.

2694
01:22:53,400 --> 01:22:55,040
An Xiaoding and An Xiaowen

2695
01:22:55,040 --> 01:22:57,040
didn't check the set?

2696
01:22:57,040 --> 01:22:58,400
An Er asked.

2697
01:22:58,400 --> 01:22:59,760
The staff confirmed it.

2698
01:22:59,760 --> 01:23:02,200
How are they not taking this seriously?

2699
01:23:02,200 --> 01:23:02,920
What if something goes wrong?

2700
01:23:02,920 --> 01:23:04,080
Forget it. I'll check it myself.

2701
01:23:04,080 --> 01:23:06,360
That's how he walked to his death.

2702
01:23:06,500 --> 01:23:08,420
(No prior entry to the set.)

2703
01:23:08,560 --> 01:23:11,200
So that points to...

2704
01:23:11,200 --> 01:23:11,680
Us.

2705
01:23:11,680 --> 01:23:13,800
Jin Xiangyu and He Jiahuan.

2706
01:23:13,800 --> 01:23:14,280
Yes.

2707
01:23:14,280 --> 01:23:14,960
(Suspicion increases on Jin and He.)

2708
01:23:14,960 --> 01:23:16,440
You two were in charge

2709
01:23:16,440 --> 01:23:17,160
of the stage...

2710
01:23:17,160 --> 01:23:17,600
Setup.

2711
01:23:17,600 --> 01:23:18,400
Yeah, setup.

2712
01:23:18,400 --> 01:23:20,440
So what could they have done?

2713
01:23:20,440 --> 01:23:21,000
First,

2714
01:23:21,170 --> 01:23:22,520
(#What Jin and He could do)
get familiar with the set.

2715
01:23:22,520 --> 01:23:23,160
Second,

2716
01:23:23,160 --> 01:23:25,040
make the wooden structure movable.

2717
01:23:25,040 --> 01:23:26,000
Yeah.

2718
01:23:26,000 --> 01:23:28,160
And hide a crossbow inside the pot.

2719
01:23:28,160 --> 01:23:30,040
Then I'm cleared.

2720
01:23:30,040 --> 01:23:32,160
That requires technical skill.

2721
01:23:32,160 --> 01:23:34,040
Who's the tech expert here?

2722
01:23:34,380 --> 01:23:36,980
(What kind of mom are you?)

2723
01:23:37,000 --> 01:23:37,800
Alright, next.

2724
01:23:38,200 --> 01:23:39,960
The shoot plan for the 24th

2725
01:23:39,960 --> 01:23:40,640
is finalized.

2726
01:23:40,640 --> 01:23:41,920
I've picked my position.

2727
01:23:41,920 --> 01:23:43,240
You can choose yours.

2728
01:23:43,240 --> 01:23:45,000
So on the 23rd,

2729
01:23:45,600 --> 01:23:47,400
we chose our positions.

2730
01:23:47,400 --> 01:23:50,520
An Xiaoding picked spot 4.

2731
01:23:50,520 --> 01:23:52,000
An Xiaowen picked spot 5.

2732
01:23:52,000 --> 01:23:53,440
He Jiahuan wanted to stand
next to his wife,

2733
01:23:53,440 --> 01:23:54,320
so he took spot 6.

2734
01:23:54,320 --> 01:23:55,360
Jin Xiangyu picked spot 1.

2735
01:23:55,360 --> 01:23:56,360
An Xiaoning picked spot 3.

2736
01:23:57,200 --> 01:23:58,480
An Ke picked spot 2.

2737
01:23:58,660 --> 01:24:00,940
(1. Jin; 2. Ke; 3. Ning;
4. Ding; 5. Wen; 6. He; An Er)

2738
01:24:00,940 --> 01:24:03,260
(Rotating lens installed
between spots 4 and 5.)

2739
01:24:03,280 --> 01:24:05,200
You two just kept replying "okay."

2740
01:24:05,200 --> 01:24:07,320
Xiaowen and Xiaoding

2741
01:24:07,320 --> 01:24:09,120
never responded.

2742
01:24:09,120 --> 01:24:09,920
We didn't have time

2743
01:24:09,920 --> 01:24:11,440
(No prior entry for Wen and Ding.)
to install

2744
01:24:11,440 --> 01:24:12,560
the mechanism

2745
01:24:12,560 --> 01:24:14,240
because we never went there.

2746
01:24:14,240 --> 01:24:14,920
So you two

2747
01:24:14,920 --> 01:24:16,560
were just the executors.

2748
01:24:19,240 --> 01:24:20,320
Here's the thing.

2749
01:24:20,320 --> 01:24:22,680
One of us installed

2750
01:24:22,680 --> 01:24:24,440
(Jin or He installed it?)
the mechanism,

2751
01:24:24,440 --> 01:24:27,440
and one of them

2752
01:24:27,440 --> 01:24:28,160
(Ding or Wen triggered it?)
triggered it.

2753
01:24:28,160 --> 01:24:28,840
Yes.

2754
01:24:28,840 --> 01:24:30,360
There's a conspiracy.

2755
01:24:30,360 --> 01:24:31,080
A conspiracy.

2756
01:24:31,080 --> 01:24:31,960
There's a conspiracy.

2757
01:24:31,960 --> 01:24:32,740
(How did the conspiracy happen?)

2758
01:24:34,180 --> 01:24:35,890
(Anyone home?)

2759
01:24:36,240 --> 01:24:36,760
Yes!

2760
01:24:36,760 --> 01:24:37,440
Who is it?

2761
01:24:37,510 --> 01:24:39,300
(An Er's autopsy report has arrived.)

2762
01:24:39,340 --> 01:24:40,380
(I left at the door.)

2763
01:24:42,560 --> 01:24:43,880
Where's the autopsy report?

2764
01:24:44,440 --> 01:24:45,240
The autopsy report.

2765
01:24:45,240 --> 01:24:46,800
(An Er's autopsy report)

2766
01:24:46,800 --> 01:24:47,320
Come on.

2767
01:24:48,260 --> 01:24:50,500
(An Er's autopsy report)

2768
01:24:50,520 --> 01:24:53,520
The deceased, An Er,
had a needle embedded in his chest.

2769
01:24:53,520 --> 01:24:55,400
The needle was coated
with a highly toxic poison.

2770
01:24:55,680 --> 01:24:57,160
This is likely

2771
01:24:57,160 --> 01:24:58,040
a poisoned needle.

2772
01:24:58,040 --> 01:24:59,000
(A poisoned needle, just as expected.)
A poisoned needle?

2773
01:24:59,000 --> 01:24:59,600
Yes.

2774
01:24:59,880 --> 01:25:01,440
This poison is colorless and odorless.

2775
01:25:01,440 --> 01:25:03,320
Death occurs immediately
after poisoning.

2776
01:25:03,320 --> 01:25:04,560
Further examination revealed

2777
01:25:04,560 --> 01:25:06,600
that the victim, An Er,
had suffered an electric shock.

2778
01:25:06,600 --> 01:25:08,040
(The victim, An Er, had suffered
an electric shock.)

2779
01:25:08,040 --> 01:25:08,680
(Had suffered an electric shock.)
Electric shock.

2780
01:25:08,680 --> 01:25:09,480
Electric shock.

2781
01:25:09,480 --> 01:25:10,940
(The victim, An Er,
had suffered an electric shock.)

2782
01:25:10,960 --> 01:25:12,400
The cause of death
was likely this needle.

2783
01:25:12,920 --> 01:25:15,080
The victim, An Er,
had suffered an electric shock.

2784
01:25:15,520 --> 01:25:17,400
(Autopsy Report)
Unable to determine cause of death.

2785
01:25:17,400 --> 01:25:18,560
Further analysis required.

2786
01:25:18,560 --> 01:25:19,000
(A new clue has surfaced
in the case!)

2787
01:25:19,000 --> 01:25:20,500
This suggests two possible
methods of murder.

2788
01:25:20,580 --> 01:25:23,140
